From d76dcb2e007902519b4056542c6bde7bdaaa2bb2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gr8day Dev <dev@havagr8day.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 22:23:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Weekly Draw Entry system (#33)

Reward every completed Gr8Day deed with weekly-draw entries (default 1/deed),
not just bingos. Bingos become a configurable bonus (default 10/bingo).
Entries are tracked as per-player balances (not ticket rows), with an
append-only ledger that serves as both audit trail and idempotency key.
The weekly draw selects a winner by weighted random on active entries.

New:
- supabase/migrations/20260625000000_weekly_draw_entry_system.sql
    player_draw_balances + draw_entry_ledger tables; SECURITY DEFINER RPCs
    (award/reverse/adjust/winner-reset/expire/backfill); 10 settings seeded.
- supabase/functions/_shared/draw_logic.ts  (pure, unit-tested logic)
- supabase/functions/_shared/draw.ts        (Supabase service + weekly draw)
- supabase/tests/draw_rules.sql             (SQL rule tests)
- supabase/tests/draw_logic.test.ts         (pure-logic tests)
- docs/weekly-draw-entry-system.md          (summary, risks, deploy steps)

Changed:
- supabase/functions/game/index.ts
    recordCompletedDeed returns the new id; mark-cell / quick-tap / dare-spin
    award deed entries; bingo transitions award the bonus; new admin endpoints
    (draw-leaderboard, reverse-deed, draw-adjust, run-draw).
- supabase/functions/weekly-reset/index.ts
    delegates to the shared, balance-based weighted draw.

Fixes two latent bugs:
- weekly-reset read game_configs with wrong column names (key/value vs
  config_key/config_value), so recent-winner odds silently used defaults.
- dare-spin auto-mark never recorded the completed deed, so those deeds were
  invisible to the Impact Board (and the draw). Now recorded and awarded.

All 15 spec test cases pass (SQL + logic suites), verified against
PostgreSQL 16 with existing migrations loaded.
